full_description: Our Story The video showcases the product in use. The video guides you through product setup. The video compares multiple products. The video shows the product being unpacked. With over 30 years of experience in the optics industry, Carson’s product line has grown exponentially to encompass a wide range of products and accessories that reflect the needs of its customers. Carson has a dedicated team of engineers whose sole mission is to improve the customer experience. Carson MicroBrite Plus Pocket Microscope! Discover, learn, and explore the wonders of the natural world with the Carson MicroBrite Plus LED Lit Pocket Microscope! With up to 120x magnification and LED lighting, kids, adults, students and professionals alike can witness the tiniest details come to life in this powerful portable tool. 60x - 120x Pocket Microscope MicroBrite Plus Handheld and Portable LED Lit for Bright & Clear Images Lab Tested Magnification Our team of Engineers personally test each and every one of our optical products for 100% magnification accuracy. Don't be fooled by what you see! LED Lighting Reveal all the hidden details with our advanced LED lighting system! Built in bright LED lights help you observe clear, detailed images with ease. 60x - 120x Zoom Magnification With a versatile magnification range, the MicroBrite adapts to your needs with precision. Adjust the zoom of your MicroBrite for stunning accuracy! For Best Results... Microscope Base must be flush against a flat viewing surface, with the LED Light turned on to provide the highest clarity images in your studies. Other Carson Microscopes! 60x - 120x Magnification Range Slides Included Phone Clip Included Additional UV Light See Everyday Objects See Slides 100x - 250x 20x - 60x MicroBrite Pro MicroFlip MicroFlip Bundle PocketMicro Learn More Does this pocket microscope work on 3D (not flat) objects? YES, but practice focusing and examining flat objects first. A 3D object will work if placed near (but not inside) the bottom of microscope (clear part), but if you pre-focus the microscope on a flat object first, it will be much easier. I'm looking at an object like a stamp and image is upside down / reversed. Is that right? YES, most microscopes do this. For handheld microscopes, the optical system flips and reverses the image, while magnifying it. This allows for an affordable and compact design. The microscope isn't broken, that's just how a pocket microscope works What kind of things can I review with this microscope? The MicroBrite can examine a diverse range of subjects, such as fabric, grass, sand, hair, skin, bugs, stamps or even a pineapple or worm! You can even observe larger microorganisms like bacteria, blood, germs, paramecium and euglena! Can I use a smartphone with this microscope to take images and video? The MM-300 version does not have a smartphone adapter, but you can buy the MM-310 adapter separate to work with it OR you can buy the MM-350 that comes with both the microscope and the smartphone adapter. How do I get the best image when focusing with this portable microscope? Always practice focusing on a flat object at the lowest power setting. Slowly turn the knob until you get close to seeing a focused image. Then turn the knob extremely slowly to get the perfect focus. Then up the power setting and slightly refocus.

full_description: Balancing Image Stability and Detail. Turning choices into win-win situations Spotting birds and small wildlife can be challenging due to their fast and flexible mobility. So higher zoom levels can cause image instability. But experienced birders know that 10x magnification strikes the perfect balance between capturing details and tracking moving targets. It allows you to observe intricate features without losing sight of your target. Yep, this is absolutely an ideal solution - A win-win that transforms the dilemma of choice into a no-brainer. Swipe right or click the button to learn more You can find simple, pure joy In today's fast-paced life filled with digital media, It's easy to overlook the simple joys around us. Grab your binoculars and step outside - the ordinary becomes extraordinary. You might spot a lively cardinal flitting between the trees or a pair of squirrels chasing each other. Each glance reveals a new wonder—adventure doesn’t require grand plans; what matters are those little moments. It’s just you, the world around you, and the simple pleasure that comes from observing. Forest Park Strolls Wandering through a forest park, there’s so much to see if you have the right tools. HONTRY compact binoculars bring the woodland alive—turning bird calls into visual experiences and distant rustles into moments of discovery. You can spot deer hiding in the shadows or birds singing from the treetops. Each stroll becomes an interactive adventure, making your connection to the forest deeper and more vivid. Hiking Exploration On a mountain hike, the views can be spectacular, but the small details often go unnoticed. With HONTRY binoculars, each hike transforms into an exciting journey of discovery. You can watch eagles soar between the peaks, examine wildflowers dotting the distant hills, or observe other hikers from afar. The binoculars’ lightweight design makes them easy to carry, and every trail becomes a richer, more immersive experience. On a cruise ship While on a cruise, the endless ocean and distant coasts can be mesmerizing, but with HONTRY compact binoculars, those distant wonders come alive. Spot dolphins playing in the waves or watch distant ships on the horizon in perfect detail. From towering cliffs to seabirds flying above, your binoculars make every ocean scene an up-close adventure, adding depth and excitement to every moment aboard. Backcountry trekking While out hiking, you spot a deer grazing quietly in the clearing ahead. You’d love a closer look, but getting too near might scare it off. That’s when your HONTRY compact binoculars come in handy. Without taking a step, you bring the deer into sharp focus, watching its gentle movements without disturbing the scene. The binoculars let you appreciate the moment in detail, savoring the experience while letting nature stay at peace. Tiny But Mighty. Pocket-Sized Power Hitting the road, taking a trip, or just cruising around? Due to Hontry compact binoculars' lightweight and portable nature, you can easily check out wildlife, admire the scenery, and especially spot potential hazards from afar - even you can find some new things in airport lounges or your backyard. They're small enough just a bit bigger than your wallet, so they won't weigh down your backpack or your Jacket. For added convenience, they come with a neck strap and a carrying case. Real Binoculars for Growing Explorers. Remember your little one, wide-eyed and curious, exploring the backyard at 3-5 years old? Or your 8-12 year old, embarking on their first National Park adventure, eager to spot wildlife? With adjustable pupil distance from 60mm to 75mm, these binoculars grow with your kids, offering a comfortable fit for everyone, from little explorers to grown-ups. So those moments when your kids excitedly hands them to you for a closer look - just adjust the angle to share the wonder and spark a conversation! Your backyard is quite something Your backyard is truly a spectacle. You and your kids will transform it into a magical fairyland. Together, you can discover birds nesting in the trees, insects hiding in the grass, and the traces of distant squirrels and raccoons. The HONTRY binoculars turn ordinary moments into opportunities for imagination and exploration—right from the comfort of your home. The view from the train window Breathtaking views from your window As you and your children admire the views from a train window, HONTRY binoculars bring the scenery to life. From the comfort of your seats, you can enjoy the passing landscape, distant mountains, and wildlife. These binoculars turn a simple train ride into an exciting adventure, enhancing the journey and sparking curiosity. Rediscovering the familiar. Not only a tool for specific outdoor activities Your backyard or neighborhood might be your familiar territory, a place you've seen countless times. With Hontry binoculars, that familiar space transforms into a captivating microcosm teeming with hidden wonders. An ordinary tree could become a haven for colorful songbirds - Spider is an artist, birds are ballerinas, and understand why kids told you that squirrel is the boss. We encourage a mindful approach to everyday life, allowing you to appreciate the hidden artistry in the ordinary. Dusk? More Like "Let's Keep Exploring!" See Clearly in Low Light Don't let fading light cut your adventures short. These binoculars feature powerful prisms for enhanced viewing in low light conditions. They work effectively even with minimal natural light, allowing you to witness the world as dawn breaks or observe nocturnal activity under a moon, watch the wildlife come alive, see the birds head home, and even spot those elusive elk near the river - the fun doesn't have to stop just because the sun sets! Take turns pointing out the fascinating details Whether you're taking a stroll in the park or enjoying a short trip, having Hontry binoculars with you allows you to share the experience with your companions or even curious passersby. As you explore, you can exchange glimpses of the unique sights each of you discovers, whether it's a rare bird flitting by or an interesting landmark in the distance. This interaction not only makes every moment together more memorable but also deepens your connection with nature and those around you. Weekend Camping Escapes On the weekends, Ashley loves nothing more than heading out for a camping trip. Her compact binoculars have become her favorite camping companion, whether she’s scanning the treetops for birds or keeping an eye on the trail ahead, her binos make every trip more engaging. With these lightweight binoculars, she can easily pack them without adding bulk to her gear. For Ashley, camping isn't just about the fresh air—it's about discovering the small details of nature that others often miss. Hiking Adventures Since getting his binoculars, John hikes have taken on a new level of excitement. The lightweight design makes them easy to carry, and now he finds himself spotting wildlife that would otherwise go unnoticed. From distant eagles to small deer blending into the brush, his binoculars reveal the hidden world along the trails. Every hike feels more rewarding, offering a renewed sense of vitality as he immerses himself in the wonders of nature—something most casual hikers miss. Island Escape Disconnecting from her phone and electronics, Samantha finds solace in observing distant islands and seabirds with her binos. Her small binoculars are perfect for travel, always within reach during her seaside getaways. As she peers through the lenses, she rediscovers the beauty in the simplicity of life, watching the waves crash and the birds soar above the sea. In these moments, she reconnects with the peace and quiet that the natural world offers, appreciating life beyond the digital noise. Artistic Inspirations Mela is a sophomore art student who often uses binoculars to observe squirrels and birds. She focus on the subtle movements and behaviors of these creatures, bringing their energy and vitality into her paintings. With each detailed observation, her artwork becomes filled with life and motion, capturing moments that others might overlook. Her meticulous work brings new depth to her paintings, all inspired by her focused observations and the inspiration drawn from the natural world.

name: Celestron – SkyMaster 25X70 Binocular – Outdoor and Astronomy Binoculars – Powerful 25x Magnification – Large Aperture for Long Distance Viewing – Multi-Coated Optics – Carrying Case Included
small_description: POWERFUL 25X MAGNIFICATION: Giant astronomy binoculars feature massive 70mm objective lenses and powerful 25x magnification. These powerful binoculars are ideal for long-distance viewing of land-based subjects or astronomical observing at night. - INCLUDES TRIPOD ADAPTER: Stabilize your binocular for added comfort and shake-free views. Mount your 70mm SkyMaster binoculars on any traditional photographic tripod with the built-in tripod adapter. - BRIGHT, SHARP VIEWS WITH BaK-4 PRISMS: The SkyMaster is a favorite among those who view in dim conditions near dawn and dusk or at night for astronomy. BaK-4 prisms maximize light throughput to your eye so you see brighter, more detailed images. - DURABLE AND WATER-RESISTANT: A rubber-armored housing protects your binoculars from damage and provides a secure gripping surface. The water-resistant exterior stands up to tough conditions and unexpected rainy weather. - UNBEATABLE WARRANTY & CUSTOMER SUPPORT: Buy with confidence from Celestron, a leading optics brand in California since 1960. Your purchase includes a Celestron Limited Lifetime US Warranty & US-based expert tech support.
full_description: The Celestron SkyMaster 25x70mm binocular is the ideal choice for amateur astronomers or anyone who observes at great distances. The 70mm objective lenses have excellent light-gathering capabilities, delivering superior low-light performance, even in the dimmest conditions. Choose SkyMaster for dusk, dawn, and nighttime astronomical viewing. Moreover, the prisms inside the binocular are made of high-quality BaK-4 glass so that more light is reflected off their internal faces and passes through to the eye. The multi-coated lenses and BaK-4 prisms maximize light transmission for remarkably bright, highly detailed images. The binocular's durable exterior housing protects your SkyMaster from damage without weighing you down. Viewing through the SkyMaster binoculars is comfortable for eyeglass and non-eyeglass wearers, thanks to the foldable rubber eyecup. The SkyMaster binocular is tripod-adaptable, so you can use the built-in binocular tripod adapter to mount it on any standard photographic tripod or monopod for extended viewing or digiscoping (photography through the eyepiece). Buy with confidence from the world’s No.1 telescope brand and a leading binocular manufacturer, based in California since 1960. You’ll also receive a Limited Lifetime warranty and unlimited access to technical support from our team of US-based experts.

small_description: Microscope screen observation mode: 2.0 inch IPS color screen, you could take photos, can be viewed in real-time, and comes with storage space, which can store about 100 photos for viewing (built-in photos cannot be downloaded, but can be deleted). - Computer observation mode: Connect the computer through a Type-C cable, then open the built-in camera software on the computer to use, with a large screen for more intuitive viewing. TIP: Note that in computer usage mode, the product buttons cannot be used, which is a normal phenomenon. - Focusing mode: Fixed ultra macro, with a maximum magnification of 500x. Full charge time: 1.5 hours. Continuous working time after full charge: 1.5 hours. Requires 5V/1A charging adapter for charging (not included in the product) - 200W high definition pixels: with 2.0 inch IPS color high definition screen, realistic colors, 178 ° visual angle.
